### FINDINGS
[F-011-01] 002 did NOT standardize peck’s AC assertion format; peck requires each task AC to be automated-test verifiable and shaped as `[precondition] + [action] -> [outcome]`, while 002 explicitly scoped only self-check/failure-mode blocks and excluded AC-coverage/T1 work. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/templates/story.md:21-27`; 002: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/001-peck-teachings-adoption/002-self-check-templates/spec.md:63`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/001-peck-teachings-adoption/002-self-check-templates/spec.md:99-103`. GAP: real. VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: M. RISK: T1 coverage gate may map vague AC prose as false positives. BLAST-RADIUS: manifest `spec.md.tmpl` plus checklist verification wording. T1 prerequisite: yes.

[F-011-02] Current L1/L2 requirement ACs are verification placeholders, not assertion-shaped clauses; peck wants explicit precondition/action/outcome pairs, while spec-kit says only `[How to verify it's done]`. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/templates/story.md:25-35`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl:89-97`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl:227-235`; 002: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/001-peck-teachings-adoption/002-self-check-templates/spec.md:124-132`. GAP: real for L1/L2. VERDICT: ADOPT for L1/L2 normalization. EFFORT: S/M. RISK: non-mechanical ACs block deterministic coverage checks. BLAST-RADIUS: low, template text only unless validator parses AC shape. T1 prerequisite: yes.

[F-011-03] L3/L3+ already contain user-story Given/When/Then ACs, so the gap is not total; however their main requirements table still uses the same non-assertion `[How to verify it's done]` placeholder. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/templates/story.md:21-27`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl:445-453`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl:532-542`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl:685-693`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl:771-772`; 002: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/001-peck-teachings-adoption/002-self-check-templates/spec.md:122-132`. GAP: partial. VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: S. RISK: mixed AC formats make T1’s parser/coverage gate level-dependent. BLAST-RADIUS: L3/L3+ requirements tables and user-story AC guidance. T1 prerequisite: yes.

[F-011-04] Checklist verification confirms completion but does not require AC-to-test mapping; peck’s rule says non-automatable requirements move to Notes, while spec-kit checklist accepts “All acceptance criteria met” plus manual testing/edge cases/error scenarios. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/templates/story.md:21-23`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/templates/story.md:58-60`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/checklist.md.tmpl:69-76`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/checklist.md.tmpl:427-434`; 002: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/001-peck-teachings-adoption/002-self-check-templates/implementation-summary.md:74-97`. GAP: partial. VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: S/M. RISK: T1 can report AC coverage without proving automated-test mappability. BLAST-RADIUS: checklist testing section and any future coverage evidence rows. T1 prerequisite: yes.

[F-011-05] 002’s own implementation state does not prove shipped template normalization: it says the phase is planned/pending and files are “Planned,” while current manifest grep shows AC headings only and no self-check/failure-mode text in the manifest templates. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/templates/story.md:21-27`; 002: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/001-peck-teachings-adoption/002-self-check-templates/implementation-summary.md:51-58`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/001-peck-teachings-adoption/002-self-check-templates/implementation-summary.md:64-67`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/001-peck-teachings-adoption/002-self-check-templates/implementation-summary.md:94-98`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl:89-97`. GAP: real. VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: M. RISK: relying on 002 as “shipped” would skip a needed prerequisite. BLAST-RADIUS: planning/continuity truth plus templates. T1 prerequisite: yes.

### RULED_OUT
- Not net-new: spec-kit already has an Acceptance Criteria column for requirements across levels, so T1 does not need to invent an AC location. `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl:89-97`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl:227-235`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl:445-453`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl:685-693`
- Not net-new: L3/L3+ already model Given/When/Then user-story ACs, so the reusable direction is format tightening, not wholesale replacement. `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl:526-542`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl:765-772`
- Not net-new: checklist already has a verification home for “All acceptance criteria met”; missing part is automated-test/test-map specificity. `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/checklist.md.tmpl:69-76`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/checklist.md.tmpl:427-434`

